  "body": "<!--\r\n  Note: if the issue is about documentation or the website, please file it at:\r\n  https://github.com/reactjs/reactjs.org/issues/new\r\n-->\r\n#### Can the event handler support get the second param, it is current instance ?\r\nusually , we write a component link follow:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nclass Component extends React.Component{\r\n    constructor(){\r\n         super()\r\n         // if we don't bind ,when the handler be called, it's `this` isn't the current instance\r\n         this.handler = this.handler.bind(this) \r\n    }\r\n    handler(event){\r\n       this.setState({})\r\n    }\r\n    render(){\r\n         return <div onClick={this.handler}>Click me !</div>\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nor we can write link follow:\r\n```js\r\nclass Component extends React.Component{\r\n    constructor(){\r\n         super()\r\n    }\r\n    handler = (event) => {\r\n       this.setState({})\r\n    }\r\n    render(){\r\n         return <div onClick={this.handler}>Click me !</div>\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nbut babel will transform it to : \r\n```js\r\nvar Component = function (_React$Component) {\r\n     _inherits(Component, _React$Component);\r\n\r\n     function Component() {\r\n          _classCallCheck(this, Component);\r\n          \r\n          // the handler isn't a prototype's method \r\n          _this.handler = function (event) {\r\n               _this.setState({});\r\n          };\r\n\r\n          return _this;\r\n     }\r\n     //  .... other method ...\r\n     return Component;\r\n}(React.Component);\r\n```\r\n\r\nif the event handler support get current instance as the second param, we will don't worry this\r\nwe can write the handler as a **strict method** : \r\n```js\r\nclass Component extends React.Component{\r\n         constructor(){\r\n               super()\r\n         }\r\n         static handler(event, instance) {\r\n              instance.setState({})\r\n         }\r\n         render(){\r\n               return <div onClick={Component.handler}>Click me !</div>\r\n        }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nand it is compatibility to old version",
